                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/786.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Acting Consul General <persName type="from"
                            >Roberston</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 5, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your September 4, 1915. Understand four-month period payments specified in new
                    decree are the rate per annum and are payable in Constitutionalist currency. Is
                    this correct?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robertson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
